<TITLE> Govt to print extra 1 crore textbooks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com)  The government will print extra one crore secondary-level textbooks to overcome the crisis, the education minister said Wednesday. "Of the figure, printing of 40 lakh textbooks will start soon, while the rest will be printed after floating urgent tender," Nurul Islam Nahid said after a meeting with representatives from the National Curriculum and Textbook Board, publishers and a related taskforce at his office. The minister said a national committee would be formed to take steps to prevent a repeat of the crisis. Those printing institutions who have been got blacklisted for irregularities in printing textbooks will not get chances to print textbooks, Nahid said. bdnews24
